  "text": "This metallic wood-boring beetle species is recorded from a single record sampled in September of 2007 by Steve Willsey from the trail curb in the Throne Room. Adults of Acmaeodera species are commonly found on flowers where they feed on pollen and/or other floral structures [CITATION_1] ). This species is an obvious accidental in the cave.",
